In "Top Headlines," Bloomberg's 
Adam Johnson reports on today's top stories including Best 
Buy's founder is preparing an executive team to lead the 
retailer if his buyout attempt is successful, the Vix has 
fallen to a 5-year low on optimism that the European debt 
crisis won't derail a global recovery and Apple and Samsung 
square off in a California court as their patent fight reaches 
the United States. He speaks on Bloomberg Television's "Lunch 
Money." (Source: Bloomberg)  Running Time: 00:57
 